FBIS4-42962 "drweu112_h_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-112 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 GERMANY DPRK Foreign Minister Arrives in Berlin DPRK Foreign Minister Arrives in Berlin OW1006023794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0217 GMT 10 Jun 94 OW1006023794 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Berlin, June 10 KYODO -- North Korean Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam arrived in Berlin on Thursday [9 June] after visiting Ukraine. The purpose and length of his stay in Berlin is not known, but Kim headed to the Chinese Embassy in Berlin by car from the airport. North Korea has no diplomatic relations with Germany, and its interests are represented by the Chinese Embassy.
